      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISS TRIBECA (1) finished sixth last start over 2130m at Gloucester Park, beaten 45 metres, after a good third at Northam the run prior. Sure to enjoy an economical run from this draw. Finds a suitable assignment and can make amends. ROLL ON LIZZIE (3) faces the starter for the first time. By Rock N Roll World and hails from the Peter Anderson stable. A nice draw on the front line should ensure a cosy run. Was not far away in a recent trial. Makes plenty of appeal. LADY CRUNCH TIME (4) is on the radar after her last-start fourth over 2100m at Bunbury a week ago. MISTER LYNDEN (8) is a three-year-old gelding by Ride High from Im For Real on debut. Won't spend a penny from this draw but luck may play a role on the bell lap. Placed in a recent trial. Well-placed to score at his first appearance.",
